initial_story:
Firefighters and police were seen outside the office of Mike Freer MP

Police are investigating a suspected arson attack at the office of North London Conservative MP Mike Freer.

A fire broke out at the rear of the North Finchley and Golders Green MP's constituency office at around 19:00 on Christmas Eve.

The Met Police confirmed it is investigating the fire.

Mr Freer told the BBC the fire happened at the rear of the premises and no one was in the building at the time of the incident.

He continued: "The police and fire brigade were on the scene in minutes and have been incredible in their response."

London Fire Brigade (LFB) confirmed the fire started in a shed outside the office before spreading to the rest of the building.

An LFB spokesperson said: "An external shed was destroyed by fire. Part of the first, second and third floors of the property were also damaged by the blaze."

In a statement, a Metropolitan Police spokesperson said: "The cause of the fire is under investigation as it is believed it may have been started deliberately. There have been no arrests."

Pictures posted on social media showed Metropolitan Police and LFB vehicles at the premises on Sunday evening.

Mr Freer has represented the North London constituency since 2010.

He is parliamentary under-secretary of state for courts and legal services, a junior role in the Ministry of Justice.

Pictures show the fire spread to an office inside the building

Once upon a time, in a land far away, there lived a beautiful princess named Snow White. She was kind-hearted, gentle, and pure of heart. She lived in a castle with her loving parents, the king and queen.

One day, the queen looked into her magic mirror and asked, "Mirror, mirror on the wall, who is the fairest of them all?"

The mirror replied, "Snow White is the fairest of them all."

The queen was furious. She was jealous of Snow White's beauty and kindness. She wanted to get rid of Snow White and become the fairest in the land.

The queen ordered the huntsman to take Snow White deep into the forest and kill her. But the huntsman couldn't bring himself to do it. Instead, he let her go and told her to run away and never come back.

Snow White ran as fast as she could, until she came upon a cottage in the woods. She was tired and hungry, so she went inside and made herself at home.

The cottage belonged to seven dwarves. They were kind and friendly, and they welcomed Snow White into their home. They became her friends and protectors.

But the queen was still determined to get rid of Snow White. She disguised herself as an old hag and went to the cottage. She gave Snow White a poisoned apple and told her to take a bite.

Snow White took a bite and fell into a deep sleep. The dwarves were heartbroken, but they couldn't wake her up.

A handsome prince came to the cottage and saw Snow White lying on the bed. He was so in love with her beauty and kindness that he kissed her on the lips.

Snow White woke up and they lived happily ever after.
